Description: The Galactic CTF Orchestrator
 MilkyWay is a modular, version-controlled toolkit for Capture The Flag
 competitions and hackathons. It organises 50+ security tools into
 "planets" (domains) with a unified CLI, automatic version control
 (Saturn), and an AI-powered assistant (Pluto).
 .
 Planets included:
  * Mercury  — Web Security (ffuf, sqlmap, nuclei, curl)
  * Venus    — Cryptography (hashcat, openssl, encoding/decoding)
  * Earth    — Forensics (binwalk, strings, steghide, tshark)
  * Mars     — Reverse Engineering (objdump, radare2, ltrace)
  * Jupiter  — Binary Exploitation (pwntools, checksec, ROPgadget)
  * Neptune  — Cloud & Misc (aws-cli, jwt_tool, kubectl)
  * Uranus   — Mobile/IoT (apktool, jadx, frida, objection)
  * Vulcan   — Network Recon & OSINT (nmap, whois, dig)
  * Titan    — Password Attacks (hydra, crunch, wordlist mutation)
  * Pluto    — AI Assistant (Ollama / OpenAI tool suggestions)
  * Saturn   — Version Control (SQLite-backed run history)
